Looks like a pretty dumb movies that might get a few minor chuckles. And, from what I can tell, it has a horrible message of going from a life of responsibilities to total capriciousness (though I expect it will end with a lesson learned along the lines of finding balance between the two extremes).

See, if the sexes were reversed and at was a man who was recently divorced and returning to a life of partying, the character would be portrayed as being an oaf and a pig. But the same thing is probably supposed to be "empowering" or something because... woman.

I really hope that it ends in a way that shows that living a life defined by roles is unsatisfying, hedonism is ultimately destructive, but the good life is somewhere between.
